WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'GoFigure' is a Workbench game where you try to create closed
figures with the available tiles on an 11 by 11 size board.

  To play, just click on a tile, its shape will rotate by 90
degrees. To create figures, a shape must 'connect' with the shapes
of it's neighbouring tiles, in order to create a path. To close
a figure, that path must return to a tile, where the path was
started. When a figure is completed, it is removed from the board.

  Try to create the biggest figures you can, the bigger they are,
the more points you get (a figure made with 4 tiles will give you
only 1 point but a larger one can give you more than 1000
points!).

  As you play the game, additional tiles appear on the board, be
careful that the board doesn't fill up too fast because when the
board is full, the game is over.

  As you progress in the game, in addition to the normal tiles,
some tiles will rotate randomly or other 'special' tiles will
appear from time to time just to complicate the gameplay...

  Have fun!

